senses
  entry
    definition "a result"
    examples ("this situation developed in response to events in Africa")
    id oewn-11437102-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "a bodily process occurring due to the effect of some antecedent stimulus or agent"
    examples ("a bad reaction to the medicine" "his responses have slowed with age")
    id oewn-00860679-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (reaction)
  entry
    definition "a statement (either spoken or written) that is made to reply to a question or request or criticism or accusation"
    examples ("I waited several days for his answer" "he wrote replies to several of his critics")
    id oewn-06758700-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (answer reply)
  entry
    definition "the manner in which something is greeted"
    examples ("she did not expect the cold reception she received from her superiors")
    id oewn-06643359-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (reception)
  entry
    definition "a phrase recited or sung by the congregation following a versicle by the priest or minister"
    id oewn-06397225-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "the speech act of continuing a conversational exchange"
    examples ("he growled his reply")
    id oewn-07214225-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (reply)
  entry
    definition "the manner in which an electrical or mechanical device responds to an input signal or a range of input signals"
    id oewn-05220076-n
    partOfSpeech n
